Gin
Ingredients
* 2 1/2 ounces gin (or vodka)
* 1/2 ounce dry vermouth
* 1/4 to 1/2 ounce olive juice (to taste)

Garnish
* 1 or 3 olives

Directions
* Pour the gin, dry vermouth and olive brine into a cocktail shaker with  ice and stir or shake well.
* Rub the rim of a martini glass with the wedge of lemon.
* Strain the contents of the cocktail shaker into a chilled glass
* Spear 1 to 3 green olives onto a cocktail stick for a garnish.

Notes
* Taken from https://www.thespruceeats.com/dirty-martini-cocktail-recipe-759643

Vodka

Ingredients
* 6 fluid ounces vodka
* 1 dash dry vermouth
* 1 fluid ounce brine from olive jar
* 4 stuffed green olives

Directions
* In a mixing glass, combine vodka, dry vermouth, brine and olives.
* Pour into a glass over ice.
* Either drink on the rocks, or strain into a chilled cocktail glass.

Notes
* Taken from https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/32238/dirty-martini/
